GOVERNMENT OF INDIA
CABINET SECRETARIAT
New Delhi, the 5th January, 1956.
-----
The under signed is directed to inform Members of
the Council of Ministers that Shri Bali Ram Bhagat assumed
office as Deputy Minister with effect from the afternoon
of the 4th January, 1956. He will be attached to the
Ministry of Finance.
Aseniu
(A.S. Gill)
for Secretary to the Cabinet.
All Members of the Council of Ministers.
Copy forwarded to the Deputy Chairman, Planning
Commission, for information.
Copy forwarded to the Secretary to the President/
the Private Secretary to the Vice-President/the Special
Assistant to the Prime Minister/the Principal Private
Secretary to the Prime Minister, for information.
"KSG"
350 copies.
AS
(A.S. Gill)
Under Secretary to the Cabinet.
Copy forwarded to all Secretaries to the Government
of India/Chairman, Railway Board/Joint Secretary, Planning
Commission/Secretary, Community Projects Administration,
for information.
Copy forwarded to all Ministries of the Government
of India (including Ministry of Railways)/Department of
Atomic Energy/Department of Parliamentary Affairs/Planning
Commission/Community Projects Administration, for information.
5%
As-
(A.S. Gill)
Under Secretary to the Cabinet.
Copy to:-
Military Wing/Establishment Section/Administration
Section and Organisation & Methods Division.
